1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In this lesson, we will take a closer look at how we can use Row and Stack blocks to achieve our design needs.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Using the Group block is one of the cornerstones of mastering the block editor.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
When you select a Group block, you have the variations of the Group block.

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,000
The standard Group block, which gathers blocks in a container, the Row block, which arranges blocks horizontally,

5
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,000
the Stack block, which arranges blocks vertically, and the Grid block, which arranges blocks in a grid.

6
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,000
To start, let's look at some common examples of where the Row block will come in handy.

7
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Firstly, I want to show you how you can create the top section of my example with the help of a Row block.

8
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,000
So if we scroll down, we will see it's currently empty, so let's go ahead and type in forward slash row.

9
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:56,000
And then add a Row block.

10
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:59,000
And then firstly, we will add a heading and name it the 'Green House.'

11
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Then I will press enter and of course the text will now be on the right of the heading.

12
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,000
So let's go and copy the text from our example, 'Make your home a sanctuary,'

13
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:24,000
and then paste.

14
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Now we will open up our List View, select the Heading and the Paragraph block,

15
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:38,000
and then group them together using my block toolbar.

16
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Now that the text is below my heading, I would like to remove the space between the blocks.

17
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:50,000
So I'll open up my sidebar settings, make my way to Styles, and below Dimensions,

18
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:56,000
I will ensure that the block spacing is set to zero.

19
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,000
Now that the heading and the text are closer to each other, I think it looks great.

20
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:06,000
So I will close my sidebar settings and then select the Row block again in my List View.

21
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Click on the Inserter and add a Buttons block.

22
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Let's say 'Explore' and open our sidebar settings and select the outline style.

23
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Next, I would like to move the Buttons block to the right, and this is where the power of the Row block really comes to play.

24
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,000
So let's select the Row block in our sidebar settings and make our way to justification in our block toolbar,

25
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:46,000
and then select Space between items.

26
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000
And once we select that, we will notice that the Buttons block pushes to the right.

27
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Lastly, I would like to align the Buttons block to the bottom.

28
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:58,000
So let's select change vertical alignment in our block toolbar and then click on align bottom.

29
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:06,000
So as you can see, there are many design possibilities using the spacing and alignment options of the Row block.

30
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:14,000
Secondly, the Row block works very effectively for headers.

31
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:19,000
So to add a header, let's make our way to Appearance and then click on the Editor.

32
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:25,000
And this will take you to your Site Editor, where you can manage templates and add headers and footers.

33
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:32,000
Make your way to patterns, click on the plus icon next to patterns, and then select Create template part.

34
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:41,000
We'll go ahead and select header and then name it appropriately, and then click on Create.

35
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,000
Now we can build our header by first adding a Row block.

36
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Next, I will add my site logo, which I've already added to my media library.

37
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:02,000
And then enlarge it.

38
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:06,000
Once I've done that, I will press Enter.

39
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:10,000
And next to my site logo, I'm going to add my Site Tagline block.

40
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:19,000
'Better beans, better coffee.' Then I'll open up my List View, select the Site Logo and the Site Tagline block,

41
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:28,000
and then wrap them in a Stack block.

42
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:32,000
Now I would like to remove the space between the two blocks, so I'll make sure I've selected my Stack block,

43
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:39,000
open up Styles in my sidebar settings, and ensure that the block spacing is zero.

44
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:46,000
And then in my block toolbar, I will also change the justification to center.

45
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:57,000
Next, I'll select my Row block, the container block, go to Styles and change the background color to salmon.

46
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:10,000
Then I'll click on the Inserter and add my Navigation block.

47
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:20,000
Now we will see a list of all the pages that I've added to my site, but I'll click on the three vertical dots and select a navigation menu that I've already created.

48
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:31,000
Then I will ensure that I select my Row block again, and then below layout in our sidebar settings, I will click on Space between items,

49
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:43,000
to ensure that the navigation menu moves to the right.

50
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:48,000
And now our header is done.

51
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Let's end off by taking a closer look at the Stack block.

52
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,000
In this example, we have three columns and as you will notice, there's less text or content in the left column.

53
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:07,000
I would like the background color as well as the Buttons block to push down and align with the columns in the middle and the right.

54
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:14,000
Let's see what I've done. I've stacked all the content within a column together in a Stack block,

55
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,000
and secondly, I stacked the heading as well as the paragraph together in a Stack block.

56
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:26,000
But I've left the Buttons block by itself.

57
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Next, when we select the main Stack block and open up our styles settings,

58
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:38,000
you will notice I've changed the background color of the Stack block and not the column.

59
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:45,000
And I've added some padding around the main Stack block.

60
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:50,000
The next crucial step is to change the minimum height of the stack block to 100%.

61
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:00,000
And as we did that, you would have noticed that the background color expanded and aligns with the other columns.

62
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:08,000
Next, we are also going to make sure that the Buttons block on the left aligns with the other Buttons blocks.

63
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:13,000
So, select change vertical alignment in your block toolbar and then select Space between.

64
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:21,000
And now you will see that the buttons block pushed down to align with the other columns.

65
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:27,000
These blocks may appear basic on the surface, but as you have seen, you can do a lot with them

66
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:32,000
once you start applying additional settings like space between and minimum height.

